ElasticCache:
	- IAM Authen for Redis
	- IAM policies on ElasticCache are only used for AWS API-level securty
	- Redis AUTH:
		+ password/token when create redis cluster
		+ extra level of security on top of security groups
		+ support ssl in fight encryption

Memcached:
	- supports SASL-based authen (advanced)

Patterns:
	- Lazy loading: stale data
	- write through: update redis when written in DB
	- session store: has ttl


Simple Authentication Security Layer (SASL)